Reasoning: The paper discusses properties of hierarchical clustering methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and data mining. The focus on theoretical properties suggests a likelihood of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Data Mining). The mention of modified versions of clustering methods and comparison with classical methods suggests a likelihood of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The mention of clustering also suggests a likelihood of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
